\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. P. cembra} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 1000 (1753). Tree up to 25 m; bark reddish-grey, becoming scaly on old trees. Twigs strongly pubescent with orange-brown tomentum. Bud-scales dull, with white, membranous margin. Leaves 5-8 cm × 1 mm. Cone 5-8 × 3·5-5 cm, less than 1½ times as long as wide. Seeds 12(-14) mm; wing absent, or less than 1 mm and caducous; husk hard. •{\i  Alps and Carpathians; occasionally planted for timber in N. Europe}. Au Cz Ga Ge He It Po Rm Rs(W) [Fe Is No Su].
