\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. P. peuce} Griseb., {\i Spicil. Fl. Rumel.}{\b  2:} 349 (1845). Tree up to 30 m; crown narrowly and densely pyramidal; bark grey, fissured with small scales. Twigs glabrous. Leaves 7-12 cm × 0·7 mm, rigid acute, densely crowded, forwardly directed. Cone 8-15 × 2·5 cm more or less curved. Seeds 8 × 5 mm; wing 15 mm. •{\i  Mountains of Balkan peninsula from} c. 41°{\i  to} 43°{\i  N}. Al Bu Gr Ju.
