\pard\f0\fs28 Monoecious; resiniferous trees, rarely shrubs, with spirally arranged leaves. Male and female cones made up of numerous spirally arranged scales. Scales of male cones (microsporophylls) bearing 2-8 pollen-sacs on the lower surface. Scales of female cones (megasporophylls) bearing 2-12 ovules on the upper surface; subtending scale (bract) indistinct, wholly or partially united with the cone-scale. Female cone more or less woody in fruit. Seeds winged.
