\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 1.           Sequoia}                 Endl.
\par     

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By V.H. Heywood.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Evergreen trees with irregularly whorled branches. Winter-buds scaly. Leaves of 2 kinds: those on the leading and cone-bearing twigs spirally arranged, subulate, scale-like, keeled above, appressed or slightly patent; those on the lateral twigs distichous linear to linear-oblong, flat, with 2 white stomatal bands beneath. Female cones persistent, ripening in the second year; cone-scales 15-20.
\par

