\pard\f0\fs28 Deciduous trees. Winter-buds scaly. Lateral twigs deciduous with the leaves. Leaves flat, linear; those of the persistent terminal twigs spirally arranged; those of the deciduous lateral twigs distichous and somewhat longer. Male cones in terminal panicles. Female cones globose, ripening in the first year.
